  <mainDescription>&lt;P class=MsoBodyText style=&quot;MARGIN: 6pt 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB>The Organisation&amp;nbsp;&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN>model &lt;/SPAN>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB>describes the organisational structure that is related to an underlying activity. The core element of the organisational view is the role. Role is a model element that derives from the organisational view and creates a link between the organisational and the process view. Each role is assigned to one or more people, while one person can carry out more than one role. At the same time each role can be part of an organisational unit. Roles can be hierarchically composed. Organisational units can have a hierarchical structure. For organisational units, the hierarchy represents the department structure of an enterprise, which allows to subdivide/aggregate business units. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></mainDescription>
  <purpose>The main purpose is to describe the organisation structure and to create a link with the process model</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
